data.name: label28.ToolTip
data.value:
uMod is a plugin framework that lets server owners extend and customize game behavior without modifying the game’s core files.
Run custom server plugins written in C#, Lua, Python, or JavaScript (though C# is the most common) Modify game mechanics (e.g., add teleport commands, kits, custom spawns) Create admin tools, permissions systems, economy plugins, etc. Easily manage server rules, gameplay logic, and automation
Downloads the official latest release from the Umod website. Extracts the files to the root directory used for server files. Deletes the .zip file downloaded.
More info on Umod.org

data.name: label18.ToolTip
data.value:
Carbon is A high-performance, self-updating framework with full Oxide plugin compatibility. Option offered for easy Ext.Rustedit.dll installation.
Downloads the official latest release from the CarbonMod github. Extracts the files to the root directory used for server files. Deletes the .zip file downloaded.
More info on CarbonMod.gg

data.name: pictureBox1.ToolTip
data.value:
DropLaunch was built to make Rust map testing easy, fast, and frustration-free. Enjoy building!.
Main Features First-Run Wizard: Guided setup to get you started in seconds. One-Click Setup: Automatically gets SteamCMD and the Rust server files. Auto Configuration: Generates optimized server startup files.
Drag & Drop Map Testing: Simply drag a .map file to launch a server instantly. Desktop Notifications: Stay updated with real-time file changes. Real-Time Monitoring: Detects and reloads maps on change for quick iterations.
Client & Server Cleanup: Removes old map files to keep test runs clean.
Instant Join: Copies connect command to clipboard for fast server entry.
Map History: View and relaunch previously tested maps.
Build, test, and play — effortlessly with DropLaunch.
